Steps to create a lightning web component and push it to scratch org:

1. set the path to the folder ---- cd E:\SALESFORCE\Vs Code

2. Create a project -------  sfdx force:project:create --projectname lwc-hello-world

3.Goto that project ------ cd lwc-hello-world

4.uthorize your Dev Hub only the first time you work on a project------- sfdx force:auth:web:login

5.Create a Default Scratch Org ---- sfdx force:org:create -s -f config/project-scratch-def.json -a "lwchelloworld"

6.Create a Lightning Web Component ------ cd force-app/main/default/lwc 
                                  ------- sfdx force:lightning:component:create --type lwc -n helloWorld -d force-app/main/default/lwc

7.create a hello world component
       ---  Add this code to the helloWorld.js file.

					 import { LightningElement, api } from 'lwc';

				export default class HelloWorld extends LightningElement {
				@api name;
				}		 
											
			------Add this code to the helloWorld.html file.

						<template>
				<lightning-card title="HelloWorld" icon-name="custom:custom14">
					<div class="slds-card__body slds-card__body_inner">
						Hello, {name}!
					</div>
				</lightning-card>
				</template>				

---------xml file

     <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<LightningComponentBundle xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata" fqn="anotherComponent">
    <apiVersion>45.0</apiVersion>
    <isExposed>true</isExposed>
    <masterLabel>Hello World</masterLabel>
    <description>Add a classic greeting to any page.</description>
    <targets>
      <target>lightning__AppPage</target>
    </targets>
    <targetConfigs>
      <targetConfig targets="lightning__AppPage">
          <property name="name" type="String" label="Name" placeholder="World" description="Enter the name of the person to greet."/>
      </targetConfig>
    </targetConfigs>
</LightningComponentBundle>


8.Push Source to the Scratch Org -------- sfdx force:source:push

9.Open the scratch org ------- sfdx force:org:open

10.Add the Component to a Lightning Page
		In the scratch org, in Setup, enter bui and click Lightning App Builder.
		To create a Lightning page, click New.
		Select App Page and click Next.
		Enter the label Hello World.
		Select Three Regions and click Finish.
		Drag the Hello World component from the Custom list of components to a region on the page.				
		Select the component and enter a Name.
		Drag more Hello World components to the page, and set a different name for each component.
		When your page is complete, click Save and Activate.
		On the Activation page, select an icon, then click Lightning Experience, and add the page to the Lightning Bolt app. Click Save.
		To exit Lightning App Builder, click Back.
		From the App Picker, click Bolt Solutions.
		Click the Hello World tab to see your page and all its greetings.
    
  11. deploy lightning component to developer org
    sfdx force:source:deploy -p <lightning component path> -u <developer org user name>
